article.headline: Long Beach State 84, CS Northridge 73
article.story: LONG BEACH, Calif. (AP) -- Aaron Nixon scored a career-high 22 points and Jibril Hodges added 19 points to lead Long Beach State to a 84-73 victory over Cal State Northridge Sunday. The 49ers snapped a six-game losing streak to the Matadors and defeated Cal State Northridge for the first time since February 2002. After trailing by 20 points in the first-half, the Matadors cut the 49ers lead to 71-66 with more than three minutes remaining in the game after Jonathan Heard's basket. But Nixon and Hodges combined for 13 points in the final three-minutes to secure the win. Dominique Ricks scored 12 points and Louis Darby added 10 points for the 49ers. Thomas Shewmake led the Matadors with 14 points. Heard had 13 points and Calvin Chitwood 12 points. The Matadors committed 21 turnovers. The 49ers held the Big West leading scorer (20.8 points per game), Mike Efevberha, to 10 points. Long Beach State (7-8, 2-2) has won five of their last seven games and improved to 6-2 at home. Cal State Northridge (6-8, 1-3) fell to 1-6 on the road.
